HEADWORD: Dermatogen
<hw>Der*mat"o*gen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>de`rma</grk>, <grk>-atos</grk>, skin + <ets>-gen</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Nascent epidermis, or external cuticle of plants
in a forming condition.</def>⟦br⟧
